  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And if any man lie with her at all,.... Not presumptuously but ignorantly, as Aben Ezra observes; for he was guilty of cutting off, that lay with her wilfully, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 20:18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and her flowers be upon her; or, \"her separation\" (k), her monthly courses not being ceased: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "he shall be unclean seven days; and be excluded from all conversation civil and religious: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and all the bed whereon she lieth shall be unclean; that and every thing upon it; and this uncleanness also lasted seven days, as Aben Ezra notes, and defiled others, though it is not written. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(k) \"menstruum ejus\", Pagninus, Montanus; \"separatio ejus\", Drusius. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(k) \"menstruum ejus\", Pagninus, Montanus; \"separatio ejus\", Drusius. ",
